OL,3,CSMA explained: The rare genetic
OL,4,Ccondition affecting Jesy Nelson's twins
OL,6,FMost types of SMA are caused by an
OL,7,Faltered gene called SMN1, which is
OL,8,Fpassed on to a child by their parents.
OL,10,FThe parents usually do not have SMA
OL,11,Fthemselves, and in most cases, SMA can
OL,12,Fonly be passed on if both parents
OL,13,Fcarry the altered gene.
OL,15,FParents usually do not have SMA
OL,16,Fthemselves but carry the altered gene.
